   as in the examples contained in the table below.


==== Examples ====
The next table provides examples of closed-form formulas for the component sequences found computationally (and subsequently proved correct in the cited references ) 
in several special cases of the prescribed sequences, 
  
    
      
        
          j
          
            n
          
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle j_{n}}
  , generated by the general expansions of the J-fractions defined in the first subsection. Here we define 
  
    
      
        0
        <
        
          |
        
        a
        
          |
        
        ,
        
          |
        
        b
        
          |
        
        ,
        
          |
        
        q
        
          |
        
        <
        1
      
    
    {\displaystyle 0<|a|,|b|,|q|<1}
   and the parameters 
  
    
      
        R
      
    
    {\displaystyle R}
  , 
  
    
      
        α
        ∈
        
          
            Z
          
          
            +
          
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle \alpha \in \mathbb {Z} ^{+}}
   and 
  
    
      
        x
      
    
    {\displaystyle x}
   to be indeterminates with respect to these expansions, where the prescribed sequences enumerated by the expansions of these J-fractions are defined in terms of the q-Pochhammer symbol, Pochhammer symbol, and the binomial coefficients.

The radii of convergence of these series corresponding to the definition of the Jacobi-type J-fractions given above are in general different from that of the corresponding power series expansions defining the ordinary generating functions of these sequences.


== Examples ==

Generating functions for the sequence of square numbers an = n2 are:


