            1
            
              1
              −
              
                x
                
                  i
                
              
              
                y
                
                  j
                
              
            
          
        
        .
      
    
    {\displaystyle \prod _{i=1}^{r}\prod _{j=1}^{c}{\frac {1}{1-x_{i}y_{j}}}.}
  In the bivariate case, non-polynomial double sum examples of so-termed "double" or "super" generating functions of the form 
  
    
      
