    {\displaystyle \left[{\begin{matrix}n\\k\end{matrix}}\right]\equiv {\binom {\lfloor n/2\rfloor }{k-\lceil n/2\rceil }}{\pmod {2}},}
  and consequently shows that 
  
    
      
        
          [
          
            
              
                
                  n
                
              
              
                
                  k
                
              
            
          
          ]
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle \left[{\begin{matrix}n\\k\end{matrix}}\right]}
   is even whenever 
  
    
      
        k
        <
        
          ⌈
          
            
              n
              2
            
          
          ⌉
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle k<\left\lceil {\frac {n}{2}}\right\rceil }
  .
Similarly, we can reduce the right-hand-side products defining the Stirling number generating functions modulo 
  
    
      
